@flexiarg coordination/artifact-registration
@title Artifact Registration (G2)
@keywords artifact, registration, graph, provenance
@audience coordination maintainers, futon3b builders
@tone formal-analytic
@references [futon-theory/proof-path futon-theory/stop-the-line]

! conclusion:
  If you want validation and durability to be meaningful, require execution to emit a registered artifact record with stable identifiers and provenance.

  + context: "Something happened" is not enough; we need an artifact we can point to.
  + IF:
    you want later gates to validate outcomes and persist evidence

  + HOWEVER:
    without an artifact record, later gates cannot refer to the product of execution

  + THEN:
    make artifact registration an explicit G2 output, and treat missing artifacts as a gate failure

  + BECAUSE:
    artifact identity is the join-key that makes PSR→PUR→PAR compositional

